| Item | Content |
|---|---|
| Product Name | Hoteling |
| Product Type | Hotel Booking Cancellation Prediction & Operational Decision Support Tool |

---

## 1. Product Overview

### 1.1 One-Line Summary
Team E provides a decision support tool that predicts booking-specific cancellation probabilities using hotel reservation data, helping hotel staff prioritize which bookings to review first.

### 1.2 Development Background
Hotel booking cancellations create uncertainty in room inventory management, customer service, resale preparation, and expected revenue. As booking volumes increase, it becomes difficult for staff to review every reservation with equal attention, and reacting only after a cancellation occurs leaves insufficient lead time. Hoteling aims to compute cancellation probabilities in advance using 15 core features available at the time of booking, establishing clear review priorities for hotel staff.

### 1.3 Product Vision
To integrate booking cancellation predictions directly into staff workflows, enabling consistent, data-driven reviews. Predictions are not used for automated decision-making; final judgments and operational actions remain fully with the staff.

---

## 2. Problem Statement

### 2.1 Current Problems
- Hotel staff struggle to identify high-risk cancellations beforehand using a consistent standard among numerous bookings.
- Late awareness of cancellations reduces the lead time required for guest verification and room resale preparation.
- Reviewing all bookings equally results in inefficient allocation of staff time and outreach resources.

### 2.2 Root Causes
- Booking cancellations are influenced by a complex combination of variables, including lead time, deposit type, market segment, average daily rate, past cancellation history, stay duration, and guest country of origin.
- Reservation details are scattered across multiple fields, making it difficult for humans to compare variable combinations simultaneously.
- Fixed rules or single-condition heuristics fail to capture diverse booking patterns effectively.

### 2.3 Core Problem
The system must provide data-driven cancellation probabilities so staff can identify high-priority bookings within limited working hours and prepare follow-up actions earlier.

---

## 3. Goals & Non-Goals

### 3.1 Product Goals
- Provide booking-specific cancellation probabilities and predictions based on 15 reservation features.
- Enable staff to query and view bookings sorted by cancellation risk.
- Display prediction results alongside the 15 input features on a single screen.
- Retain final judgment and operational authority exclusively with human staff.

### 3.2 User Goals
- Identify high-risk cancellation bookings first.
- Initiate customer verification or room resale preparation earlier.
- Decide on appropriate actions after reviewing cancellation probabilities in context with the 15 features.
- Track prediction results and staff action histories.

### 3.3 Technical Goals
- Train and manage 15-feature candidate models (XGBoost, Random Forest, Logistic Regression, etc.) using time-series cross-validation.
- Enforce identical 15-feature definitions and preprocessing rules across training and inference.
- Monitor F1-Score as the primary metric, alongside ROC-AUC, Accuracy, and Recall as target performance metrics.
- Maintain traceability for input data, preprocessing pipelines, and model versions.

### 3.4 Out of Focus (Non-Goals)
- No automated cancellation of bookings based solely on prediction scores.
- No automated adjustments to room rates or refund policies.
- No automated outreach or messaging to guests.
- No automated decisions that could disadvantage guests.
- No guaranteed improvements in overall revenue, occupancy, or cancellation rates within the current scope.

