## 7. AI & Data Requirements

### 7.1 Data Scope
- Utilizes City Hotel reservation records from the public Hotel Booking Demand dataset.
- Raw City Hotel dataset contains 79,330 records.
- Cleaned dataset used for modeling contains 78,669 records.
- Dataset timeframe spans from July 2015 to August 2017.

### 7.2 Target Variable
| Item | Value |
|---|---|
| Variable Name | `cancellation` (or `is_canceled`) |
| Type | Categorical Binary |
| Value 0 | Not Canceled |
| Value 1 | Canceled |

### 7.3 AI Model Input Features (15 Features)

| No. | Feature Name | Type | Description |
|---:|---|---|---|
| 1 | `lead_time` | Continuous | Number of days between booking date and arrival date |
| 2 | `num_nights_weekend` | Continuous | Number of weekend nights stayed |
| 3 | `num_nights_week` | Continuous | Number of week nights stayed |
| 4 | `meal_type` | Categorical | Type of meal booked |
| 5 | `market_segment` | Categorical | Market segment designation |
| 6 | `is_repeated_guest` | Categorical | Repeated guest flag |
| 7 | `num_cancel_prev_resv` | Continuous | Number of previous canceled bookings |
| 8 | `num_checkin_prev_resv` | Continuous | Number of previous non-canceled or checked-in bookings |
| 9 | `reserved_room_type` | Categorical | Type of room reserved |
| 10 | `deposit_type` | Categorical | Type of deposit made |
| 11 | `customer_type` | Categorical | Type of customer/booking |
| 12 | `average_daily_rate` | Continuous | Average Daily Rate (ADR) |
| 13 | `num_guest` | Continuous | Total number of guests |
| 14 | `country_code` | Categorical | Customer country code |
| 15 | `arrival_month` | Continuous | Month of arrival |

### 7.4 Preprocessing Requirements
- Filter and retain City Hotel records only.
- Drop records where adult count is zero (`adults == 0`).
- Drop records where `distribution_channel` is `Undefined`.
- Exclude extreme outliers in `average_daily_rate` (`adr >= 400`).
- Remove records where the sum of week and weekend nights equals zero.
- Align data types of target and 15 input variables with the training schema.

### 7.5 Data Split Requirements
- Apply a **5-Fold Time-Series Cross-Validation** strategy to prevent temporal data leakage.
- Split the Development Set and Final Test Set chronologically.

