## 9. Non-Functional Requirements

### 9.1 Performance
- Support both single-booking real-time queries and batch data uploads.
- Establish target response time SLAs for 15-feature inference calls.
- Process batch records gracefully by separating successful rows from failed rows.

### 9.2 Reliability & Stability
- Isolate schema error rows to prevent entire batch execution failures.
- Log model and preprocessing versions to ensure full reproducibility of results.
- Ensure model inference failures never trigger automated guest actions.
- Allow staff to revert to standard manual procedures during system outages.

### 9.3 Usability
- Clearly distinguish between cancellation probabilities and predicted binary classes.
- Explicitly state that prediction results are probabilistic reference indicators, not confirmed facts.
- Provide sorting, searching, and filtering capabilities on reservation lists.
- Deliver clear error messages specifying problematic fields among the 15 features and suggested corrections.

### 9.4 Scalability & Maintainability
- Support tenant isolation for hotel-specific data and model versions.
- Maintain clean modular separation across validation, preprocessing, inference, and persistence layers.
- Establish periodic monitoring procedures for model performance and input data drift.

