## 11. Success Metrics & Completion Criteria

### 11.1 AI Model Performance Targets & Acceptance Criteria (KPIs)

* **Primary Metric**: F1-Score
* **Secondary Metrics**: ROC-AUC, Accuracy

| Metric | Minimum Acceptance Threshold | Target Goal | Evaluation Method |
| :--- | :---: | :---: | :--- |
| **F1-Score** | **≥ 0.70** | **≥ 0.75** | 5-Fold Time-Series Cross-Validation Mean |
| **ROC-AUC** | **≥ 0.85** | **≥ 0.90** | Final Test Set Evaluation |
| **Accuracy** | **≥ 0.70** | **≥ 0.75** | Overall Prediction Accuracy |

> **Acceptance Criteria**:
> 1. To minimize undetected cancellation risk (False Negatives), the model must achieve a **Recall of ≥ 0.70** on the cancellation class to be approved for production inference.
> 2. The standard deviation (SD) of ROC-AUC across cross-validation folds must remain **within 0.03** to ensure temporal stability.
> 3. Failure to meet minimum acceptance thresholds will trigger feature engineering iteration and model retraining.

### 11.2 Product Metrics
- Time required for staff to identify high-priority review bookings.
- Staff comprehension rate of prediction outputs.
- Percentage of predicted high-risk bookings actually reviewed by staff.
- Rate of unnecessary guest outreach incidents.
- Ratio of actual cancellations that were pre-identified and reviewed.

### 11.3 Completion Criteria
- Feature names and data types of all 15 inputs match between training and inference schemas.
- Preprocessing pipeline versions and time-series data split parameters are locked.
- AI model artifacts are version-controlled and responding to inference calls.
- End-to-end flow from input validation to prediction display is operational.
- Prediction outputs and model versions are stored correctly.
- Basic user workflows are validated against target user scenarios.

